es and precursors as Thomas Berry, Leonardo Boff, Holmes Rolston III, Ken Wilber, and Edgar Morin. Also included is research across the social sciences, biophysical sciences, and humanities discussing multiple worldviews and perspectives related to integral ecologies. The Variety of Integral Ecologies is both an accessible guide and an advanced supplement to the growing research for a more comprehensive understanding of ecological issues and the development of a peaceful, just, and sustainable planetary civilization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEcological integrity. 0aEcologyxStudy and teaching. 0aEnvironmental sciences. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Ecology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Psychology. 4aPsychology : Integral Theory. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Environment and Religion. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh1 aAllison, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsbjörn-Hargens, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHathaway, Mark D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedlund, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvakhiv, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, Sean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLitfin, Karen T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMickey, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMickey, Sam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobbert, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbert, Adam, eedito